> 70 is way different than a 77. You have a threaded cap, no? 70 is way
bigger, and cams into place with 3 tabs.

I didn't know that they were different.  No threaded cap on G, just a hole
with two notches to catch the tabs on the OEM cap.

The locking one that we picked up from AZ is made by MotoRad.  It's has
four
tabs, two to keep the cap from rotating, and two to lock it in place.  It's
outer circumference is large enough to fill up the entire gas cap
depression
in the body.--
